description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI Thailand IMI 25/50 Index.
 The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The index consists of stocks traded primarily on the Stock Exchange of Thailand. A capping methodology is applied to issuer weights so that no single issuer of a component exceeds 25% of the index weight, and all issuers with weight above 5% do not cumulatively exceed 50% of the index weight. It is non-diversified.
